<TEXT>
the environmental mess that has plagued 
eastman kodak co for nearly a year may be more a result of emotions 
and coincidences than pollution and poisons 
no one can say for sure 
but the company once considered the benevolent corporate father 
who could do no wrong has certainly suffered a major blow to its 
status in its hometown 
clearly our reputation at least as an environmentally 
responsible company has been brought into question and we dont 
like that said ron roberts a company spokesman 
the whole mess started last march when a newspaper article 
disclosed that some testing by kodak indicated that chemicals had 
probably leaked from kodak park the companys sprawling 
manufacturing complex into the groundwater of a neighboring 
residential area 
wall street analysts and others took notice but quickly lost 
interest 
i think the view down here was is this going to be 
catastrophic are we talking billions or hundreds of millions of 
dollars said eugene glazer an analyst for dean witter reynolds 
inc we looked at it and the answer was no 
that left the issue to be hashed out in the community 
since the first report rhetoric and charges have been furiously 
flying in numerous public hearings and blanket media coverage a 
200 million lawsuit has been filed against the company a major 
expansion project to produce more color film has been stalled 
residents of rand street have appeared on television news 
broadcasts to detail their dizziness headaches and unexplained nose 
bleeds theyve also held news conferences and protests 
one woman even put her pet rabbit who died during the uproar in 
the freezer to save as possible proof that chemicals were moving out 
of the ground and into her home 
the way this thing was presented it sounded like kodak was 
poisoning the neighborhood said dr joel nitzkin director of the 
monore county health department its all been taken out of 
context there just isnt any evidence of any health hazard 
his department conducted studies immediately after the newspaper 
report and found nothing unusual in the rand street neighborhood 
many of the complaints were exaggerated or had common explanations 
like having a home that was too dry in the winter 
months later the health department conducted more tests in two 
schools near the manufacturing center and pronounced them safe 
yes we found contamination from the cleaning agents used in 
