the us dollar advanced in early trading monday 
against the japanese yen while prices on the tokyo stock exchange 
rose slightly 
the dollar opened at 12270 yen up 027 yen from fridays close 
of 12243 yen 
traders said the dollars rise followed its strength on the 
sydney market which opened earlier than tokyo 
a dealer at a major commercial bank said the dollar was expected 
to trade in a narrow range until wednesday when the us commerce 
department is scheduled to release the nations trade figures for 
october 
on the tokyo stock exchange the nikkei stock average of 225 
selected issues a 3452point winner friday rose 4035 points or 
013 percent to advance to 2983377 shortly after the market 
opened 
